title: Todd Terry - A Day In The Life (1995)@flac
description:
There's little question that A Day in the Life of Todd Terry is one of the best albums of Terry's pioneering house ever released -- it leads off with two of his best-known tracks, "A Day in the Life" and "I Hear the Music." 
And the rest of this compilation just reinforces his status as one of the best house producers of all time, from the uplifting vibes of "Clear Away the Past" and the tribal headrush of "Jungle Hot" to smoother tracks like "Teela's Theme." (AMG)
